Content:: The Lophophorata are a Lophotrochozoan clade consisting of the Brachiozoa and the Bryozoa.[1][2][3][4] They have a lophophore. Molecular phylogenetic analyses suggest that lophophorates are protostomes, but on morphological grounds they have been assessed as deuterostomes.[5] Cycliophora Annelida Mollusca Brachiopoda Phoronida Entoprocta Ectoprocta Nemertea  This protostome-related article is a stub.
